# This file excludes paths from the Docker build context.
#
# By default, Docker's build context includes all files (and folders) in the
# current directory. Even if a file isn't copied into the container it is still
# sent to the Docker daemon.
#
# There are multiple reasons to exclude files from the build context:
#   1. Prevent local build outputs from leaking into the image (ex: bin/ obj/).
#   2. Reduce the size of the build context and improve build time.
#   3. Avoid sending files containing sensitive information.
#
# More information on using .dockerignore is available here:
# https://docs.docker.com/engine/reference/builder/#dockerignore-file

.dockerignore

# Ignore git, but keep git HEAD and refs to access current commit hash if
# needed:
#
#   $ cat .git/HEAD | awk '{print ".git/"$2}' | xargs cat
#   d0b8727759e1e0e7aa3d41707d12376e373d5ecc
.git
!.git/HEAD
!.git/refs

# .NET build outputs — must stay out of the SDK stage's view so the in-image
# publish is reproducible from source instead of accidentally re-packing a
# host-side `dotnet build` output.
**/bin/
**/obj/
publish/
*.user
*.suo

# IDE / tooling caches
.idea/
.vs/
.vscode/
.cursor/
.cache/

# Test outputs + coverage
**/TestResults/
coveragereport/

# Node tooling (none in-repo today, future-proofing)
node_modules/

# CI + docs aren't needed inside the image build
.github/
docs/

# Legacy / unrelated artifacts left over from the Elixir-era repo
/cover/
/doc/
/test/
/tmp/
.elixir_ls
/_build/
/deps/
*.ez
erl_crash.dump
/assets/node_modules/
/priv/static/assets/
/priv/static/cache_manifest.json
